@node histAF "History of Amiga Frontier"

Amiga Frontier was first set up, back in March 1995 as a P.D library
and magazine all on one disk. Which I think was a great idea.
The P.D library did really well to start with, but after a few weeks
I found that the magazine was proving to be quite popular.
The magazine and library was all on one disk and it was available WEEKLY!
Jolly good eh?
The magazine & library worked using menumaster and PPMore. Shite I know,
but it was only a souped up cat disk!
I then moved on to Magnum V1.7, which was used for issue 1 & 2.
Issue 1 was a major sell out round here and must have sold well in 
advance of 20 copies + we distributed loads of the ourselves, so we
had a total readership of almost 50. Not bad for a start.
I then found DMC on a 17 Bit CDROM which was an old shareware release,
which asked people to register for a more upto date release, soooo....
a quick letter to Andy Gibson and 3 weeks later (he'd moved you see)
I received DMC Gold from F1 Licenseware, which I didn't even know existed.
We then received a DMC updater disk.
The likes of MSC and Molgrat joined A.F in April 1995 (when A>F was still
a cat-disk). We got up to issue 6 of the old A.F series, but we decided
to start all over again with a total revamp.
Ian Devil joined A.F in Issue 1 (the second time round).
Mega Gamer joined in from Issue 2 onwards and Log joined in issue 3
onwards.
A.F was finally sent to the P.D libraries when it reached issue 3.
We now have well in excess of 100 readers, and that figure is rising
rapidly.

After that history lesson, I have but one thing to say:

Escom are a load of wind and piss.
Thank-you & goodbye.
@endnode



@node Requirements "What you need to run A.F"

To use Amiga Frontier, you will need:

An Amiga (no shit)
1meg memory will run A.F, but strongly recommend 1.5 meg+
An Amiga 500+ should run A.F o.k, but I don't have a 500+ to test A.F on.
An Amiga 600 this is fine, we recommend 1.5 meg or more
An Amiga 1200perfect, 100% fine with 2meg machines

We regret that A.F won't run on an A500, well, I don't regret it at all
really, because they're crap. 

Recommended setup: A1200 with 2 meg + Harddrive.

Certain intros may take advantage of extra Fast Ram

Any Amiga with workbench 2.0 should work fine.

Disclaimer: If A.F, The hard-drive installer or AmigaGuide docs
            should crash your machine or result in any data loss.
            DON'T blame us. We test A.F on various A1200's with and
            without hard-drives and it is fine.


A.F has been tested on many A1200 configurations, from 2Meg with no
hard-drive to an A1200 with 6Meg, 1Gig Hard-drive and an 030 + 68882.
It works fine. I have also been told that A.F is fine on an A4000 040
and A4000 030.


Not tested:                                     

A1200 with overdrive hard-drive
A3000
A2000
A500+   <--- should work

@endnode





